## Router.resolve property

Returns the [normalized version](./reactivuety.routelocation.md) of a [route location](./reactivuety.routelocationraw.md)<!-- -->. Also includes an `href` property that includes any existing `base`<!-- -->.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
resolve: (to: RouteLocationRaw) => RouteLocation & {
        href: string;
    };
```
